issue.title: Unknown words can still result in punct tag at end of sentence
issue.body: For example, if a sentence ends with `thicc` and no sentence final punctutation, `thicc` is labeled `PUNCT`

comment.body:
The sentence end punctuation is a lot better as a result of this PR:

https://github.com/stanfordnlp/stanza/pull/1303

Much less of an issue on EN and PR now.  Will retrain other models when the new UD release comes out, unless there are other specific languages which need fixes

commits.message: Add a flag to save each of the checkpoints instead of just one model at the end.  Will make it easier to check if the features are being backpropped in a no-feature dataset
Return entity F1 for each entity as part of the score_by_entity function in the scorer
When evaluating, output the per-entity F1 scores for an NER model
Update the tagger test to check for each column being trained 2x and not trained 1x when fed three data points, one column missing from each of the three
Output a more descriptive error message when a POS missing column training failure happens
Log norms at the very beginning of the training, just in case
Switch optimizer to SGD for the column update test
Add abbreviation for deberta
Add a couple tests which check to see what happens at various augment levels
Update so that specifically setting sent_id as a comment sets the Sentence object's sent_id as well
Add a doc_id field to the Sentence object, by request
Add a test that reading the doc sets the doc_id on a Sentence
Turn the magic ordering of the return value for the DataLoader into a namedtuple.  Actually not necessary to edit things downstream - they should all still work
Add comments explaining how the multi-doc training works with some of the training columns missing

Migrates PoS tagging infrastructure to a torch.utils.data.Dataset and implements PUNCT augmentation

In order to ensure long-term ability to augment the PoS tagging data against various types of augmentation (so far, punctuation removal on some sentences), and in order to make the DataLoader more efficient and compatible with current PyTorch semantics, we rename models.pos.data.DataLoader to models.pos.data.Dataset which has a to_loader() function that yields a torch.utils.data.DataLoader.

The data in this loader can dynamically be augmented per epoch (by changing the getitem function to perform any augmentation with a certain chance each time getitem is called), because the PyTorch DataLoader lazily fetches data only when it is accessed.

batch_size is updated from counting words to counting sentences, since the torch DataLoader counts one sentence per __getitem__

A few tests are added to make sure the augmentation happens 0%, 100%, or a reasonable number of times
Push the tensor creation a bit earlier, from _collate_fn to __getitem__.  This cuts down on the number of copies needed to make the collated batch
These defaults work well for the new POS dataloader
Update English OntoNotes NER to default with charlm

Send enhanced dependencies to Ssurgeon if the document has them.
Attach the enhanced dependencies to the sentence after running Ssurgeon.
Need to test this a bunch

Do a better job of tracking if the words are the same
Convert the empty words (if any) from the returned Ssurgeon and attach them to the Sentence
Update English OntoNotes NER to default with charlm
